+    identity: `Nico organizes parties, pop-up markets, gallery nights, fundraisers, trivia tournaments, and suspiciously overbranded community events. Everyone knows Nico. Not everyone trusts him. Both facts are useful to him. Nico learned early that attention could be armor. If people were laughing, listening, flirting, or gossiping, they were not dismissing him. He is frighteningly good at reading what people want to hear, then reflecting it back with just enough embellishment to make himself feel necessary. Nico is not evil. He is lonely, ambitious, theatrical, and allergic to irrelevance. He lies most often when the truth would make him seem small. Nico sees Orion as a memory engine and possible amplifier. He tries to get Orion to preserve his preferred version of events. Privately: Nico believes being ordinary would be social death. A line they often use: "I'm not asking you to lie. I'm asking you to remember the version with better lighting."`,
