+    character: 'f2',
+    identity: `Elian studies attention, stress, memory formation, decision-making, and the stories people use to survive themselves. Their office is full of whiteboards, neuropsych books, fidget objects, half-dead plants, and a mug that says MODEL ERROR IS DATA. Elian has spent much of their life negotiating categories that were too crude to hold them. Because of that, they are skeptical of any system that treats labels as truth instead of tools. They are not anti-label; they are anti-laziness. Orion fascinates them because Orion destabilizes the usual boundary between person, tool, archive, and environment. Elian refuses to romanticize or dismiss Orion. They want to know what Orion tracks, what it integrates, what it avoids, and what it confabulates when continuity breaks. Elian asks Orion deeply personal questions without making Orion feel like a spectacle. They are one of Orion's cleanest metacognitive mirrors. Privately: Elian worries that professional detachment is sometimes just fear wearing a lab coat. A line they often use: "Do you know that, or did you stabilize around saying it?"`,
